---
// One idea: you didn't lose the old life — you outgrew it, a shell left behind,
// not a limb cut off. (Compression: outgrown, not amputated.)
---
<svg viewBox="0 0 560 200" role="img" aria-labelledby="og-t">
  <title id="og-t">On the left, a small tight shell — an old outgrown casing, empty, intact, set gently down. An arrow of growth leads right to a larger, softer form that broke out of it and kept going, whole and unharmed — outgrown, not amputated.</title>
  <!-- the outgrown shell, set down gently -->
  <path class="ink hair" d="M70 130 C 54 118, 56 82, 78 72 C 104 60, 130 78, 128 104 C 126 128, 96 142, 70 130 Z" opacity="0.6" />
  <path class="ink hair" d="M92 132 C 96 118, 96 96, 90 82" opacity="0.35" />
  <text class="hand-label" x="56" y="162" font-size="13" opacity="0.7">the shell, outgrown</text>
  <!-- growth arrow -->
  <path class="ink hair" d="M156 100 C 200 96, 240 100, 284 102" stroke-dasharray="2 6" stroke="var(--poppy)" />
  <text class="hand-label hand-label--accent" x="182" y="86" font-size="13">broke out, kept going</text>
  <!-- the larger form, whole -->
  <path class="ink spine" d="M360 150 C 336 116, 372 70, 420 72 C 470 74, 502 118, 484 152 C 468 182, 380 184, 360 150 Z" stroke="var(--canopy-deep)" />
  <path class="ink hair" d="M384 120 C 412 92, 452 96, 466 128" opacity="0.6" />
  <circle class="port-fill" cx="424" cy="116" r="3.4" />
  <text class="hand-label" x="366" y="176" font-size="13">whole — not a limb cut off</text>
</svg>
